    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="faq-item">
        <h5>How do I sign up to drive with Cabocab?</h5>
        <p>Download the Cabocab driver app, sign up with your name, phone number, and vehicle details, and submit the required documents for verification.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
        <h5>How do I accept a ride request?</h5>
        <p>When a ride request appears, tap “Accept” to confirm the ride.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
        <h5>What should I do if a rider cancels a trip?</h5>
        <p>If a rider cancels, you will be notified instantly, and no further action is required. You may receive a cancellation fee based on the terms.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
        <h5>How does the rating system work for drivers?</h5>
        <p>After every trip, customers can rate your service, and you can also rate customers. Ratings help build trust within the platform.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
        <h5>How do I receive payments from customers?</h5>
        <p>Payments are made directly to your bank account or in cash.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
        <h5>What safety features are available in the driver app?</h5>
        <p>The app offers an SOS button for emergencies, customer rating systems, and 24/7 customer support.</p>
    </div>
</div>
